        "id": 4670933,
        "name": "Noah C @ P U R 5 0",
        "username": "Noah_C",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/noah_c/{size}/3440_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-05-30T04:06:29.908Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I love Chablis with some age on it- and this was fantastic tonight. This is perfect right now for my taste, though it seems as if this bottling can for <a href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/t/tn-1979-domaine-louis-michel-chablis-1er-cru-vaillons/172529\">a lot longer</a>!</p>\n<p>My TN:</p>\n<p>Great stuff at 16 years old. Color is turning a bit golden. Preserved lemons, lemon curd, chalk, and sea spray on the nose. The acid is still quite high, linear, with plenty of tension. The body is a bit fuller than your typical Chablis, presumably from age, and the lemons are preserved rather than fresh. There is plenty of crushed rock and some saline character on the long lingering finish. I love Chablis with age. Just wonderful.</p>",
