        "created_at": "2025-06-03T18:50:27.925Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Monopole_Cru\" data-username=\"Mark_C_Johnson\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"336666\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/mark_c_johnson/48/866_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Mark_C_Johnson:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Many pre-mox</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I\u2019ve loved their wines for decades and still have over three cases cellared\u2014mostly Mont\u00e9e de Tonnerre, Butteaux VV, Vaud\u00e9sir, Les Clos, and Grenouilles, spanning 2012 to 2022. I haven\u2019t encountered any premox so far, though I\u2019ll admit I open more Champagne than anything else these days. Fingers crossed I\u2019m not sitting on a cider time bomb.</p>",
